1. Download 'labelImg' tool to label images
	-Go to https://tzutalin.github.io/labelImg/
	-Download Linux_v1.4.3

2. Resize Images
	-From dir models/research/1_A_v1.0
	-Use resize_img.py/resize_img_folder.py
	-Set images/images_sub_directories directory path
	-$ python resize_img_folder.py
3. Run labelImg
	-$ sudo ./labelImg
	-Open directory having images to label
	-Label all images

4. Convert images and labels to csv file
	-$ python xml_to_csv.py --image_path <LABELLED_IMGS_DIR> --csv_file <Name_of_csv_file>
	-Example: $ python xml_to_csv.py --image_path Database/1_A/labelled_images/train --csv_file labels_train.csv
	-$ python xml_to_csv.py --image_path Database/1_A/labelled_images/validation --csv_file labels_valid.csv

5. Create label.pbtxt (File containing list of all labels)(See Sample File)

6. Convert csv to tfrecord (for training and testing)
	-Generate training set
	-$ python generate_tfrecord.py --csv_input=labels_train.csv  --output_path=train.record --label_map=label.pbtxt --image_path=Database/1_A/labelled_images/train
	-Generate testing set
	-$ python generate_tfrecord.py --csv_input=labels_valid.csv  --output_path=test.record --label_map=label.pbtxt --image_path=Database/1_A/labelled_images/validation
